  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. All subjects must have a diagnosis of PD by a licensed neurologist according to the UK
             Parkinson's Disease Society Brain Bank Clinical Diagnostic Criteria (UKPDBB).(Goetz,
             2010) The UKPDBB is a 3 step diagnostic tool which defines inclusion and exclusion
             criteria for diagnosing PD

          2. between 35 and 79 years of age

          3. mentally able to participate in the study

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Pregnancy

          2. any person who is currently taking amino acid supplements.

          3. Any history of myocardial infarction, stent, or CABG

          4. Phenylketonurics

          5. Untreated hypertension
      </textblock>
